title: A plane was flying with 159 onboard. Then both pilots fell asleep.
description: The pilots were asleep for 28 minutes during the Batik Air flight in Indonesia, a preliminary report from the country’s National Transportation Safety Committee said.

title: France, worried about Olympics strikes, will pay government workers more
description: French authorities have framed this summer’s Olympic and Paralympic Games as a chance for France to shine on the global stage.

title: First official photo of Princess Catherine since surgery is released
description: Kensington Palace said the photo was taken by Prince William “earlier this week.” Catherine’s public absence after her surgery sparked widespread speculation.

title: Biden holds out hope for Ramadan cease-fire in Gaza
description: President Biden said a cease-fire during Ramadan, which begins Monday, was “possible.” But a day earlier, he said it was “looking tough” amid stalled talks.

title: Brazil’s staggering dengue fever crisis is a warning to the world
description: The disease has ripped through much of South America this year, and worse may be ahead as climate change expands the range of the mosquito carrying the virus.
